description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**This vacancy is subject to Agenda for Change Banding**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for us to recruit a Band 3 Healthcare Assistant (HCA) to further develop our Dermatology department within SaTH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Band 3 HCA to work 24 hours per week on a permanent contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be working within our outpatient department and will be supporting in the general day to day running of the clinic. Duties would include direct patient care and observations, wound and skin care, ordering stock and dealing with telephone enquiries as well as working alongside our surgeons and providing patient support in our minor operation service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Desired skills and prior knowledge would include basic wound care, dressing selection, aseptic technique and recording patient observations, however training will be provided. Previous Hospital Healthcare Assistant experience is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should be flexible, possess good time management skills, excellent communication skills and can work independently as well as in a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should possess up to date knowledge regarding infection control, information governance and safeguarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly team and are thrilled by the opportunities to develop our service. Come join our team and be part of something great!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome any interested persons contacting the department for a discussion or to arrange a visit prior to applying/interview if shortlisted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
